29/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government said Friday (27 June) that two new crossings would be opened soon on the border with Serbia-Montenegro, after a few remaining technical details are worked out. According to government spokesman Saso Colakovski, the crossings would reduce the number of violations and ease problems for those living in the border areas.
In other news, Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski and the commander of the Macedonian Army Border Brigade, Gjorgji Bojadziev, paid a visit Saturday to the Nidze watchtower, located on the border with Greece. Bojadziev described the situation there as stable. (MIA - 28/06/03; MIA - 27/06/03)
